author: Al Jazeera English
description:
The Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences has awarded the 2025 Nobel Prize in Physics to a trio of United-States-based scientists for work on quantum mechanic tunnelling.
The award, announced by the Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences on Tuesday, will be presented to John Clarke, Michel H Devoret, and John M Martinis in December “for the discovery of macroscopic quantum mechanical tunnelling and energy quantisation in an electric circuit”.
The trio’s experiments demonstrated that quantum mechanical properties can be made concrete on a macroscopic scale, the prize-awarding body said in a statement.
Their work has “provided opportunities for developing the next generation of quantum technology, including quantum cryptography, quantum computers, and quantum sensors”, it continued.

Al Jazeera’s Charlie Angela reports from London.

description:
For two years, Palestinians in Gaza are facing an escalating humanitarian crisis as Israel’s continuous bombardment forces thousands of families from their homes. 
In central Gaza, many are seeking refuge in bombed-out buildings, risking their lives in structures on the verge of collapse. 
Displaced families have been left with no choice but to live amidst the ruins of what were once homes, schools, and shops.
The destruction has displaced countless residents, with shelters becoming increasingly scarce as strikes devastate communities. 
For many, the choice is stark: remain in unsafe ruins or risk being entirely exposed. 
As the bombardment intensifies, stories of resilience emerge amidst the devastation, highlighting the dire conditions and the enduring need for safety and protection.

Al Jazeera’s Hani Mahmoud reports from Deir el-Balah, Palestine.

description:
Tuesday marks two years since the October 7 attacks that led to Israel's devastating war on Gaza.
More than 67,000 Palestinians have been killed by Israeli forces, and nearly two million displaced.
Indirect negotiations between Israel and Hamas are now underway in Egypt to finalise a ceasefire deal. 
Hamas has agreed to release all Israeli captives but says the continuous bombing of Gaza poses a challenge. 
US President Donald Trump says Hamas is agreeing to important aspects of his 20-point ceasefire plan. 

Despite those negotiations, Israel's attacks on Palestinians across Gaza persist.
Israeli forces carried out more strikes, targeting various areas of Gaza City. 
Medical sources say at least 3 Palestinians have been killed and several others wounded in the Sabra neighborhood. 
The Israeli military says it will continue its ground offensive as long as there's no ceasefire in place.

Shaina Low is a Communication Adviser for Palestine at the Norwegian Refugee Council.

description:
Meet Farah and Myriam — two young girls from Gaza.

For Farah, night means fear — a reminder of loved ones killed in the darkness.

For Myriam, her home was destroyed, taking her mother and sister. Her aunt’s body remains buried under the rubble.

She lives in a tent beside the ruins and this is where the two girls meet to share their grief, fears and hopes for the future after two years of war.

Farah and Myriam is directed by Wissam Moussa. It’s part of From Ground Zero, a collection of 22 short films made in Gaza, initiated by Palestinian director Rashid Masharawi, to tell the untold stories of the current war.

From Ground Zero was the official submission of Palestine, in the Best International Feature Film category of the 97th Academy Awards in 2025.

It comes ahead of midterm elections, seen as a test of his radical economic policies and a measure of damage done to his government by a series of scandals.

Al Jazeera’s Daniel Schweimler reports from Buenos Aires, Argentina.

description:
Leaders in the US state of Illinois are taking President Donald Trump to court, looking to stop the deployment of hundreds of National Guard troops to the streets of Chicago.
The White House argues that soldiers are needed to prevent so-called lawlessness. 
But local leaders say the real problem is Trump's sweeping crackdown on immigration.

Al Jazeera’s John Hendren reports from Chicago.

description:
The world is falling short on protecting women and girls, caught in conflict.
That's one of the key messages from a special UN Security Council meeting, which highlighted their plight in Gaza.
But there is hope for progress.

Al Jazeera’s Gabriel Elizondo reports from the United Nations.

author: Al Jazeera English
description:
Indirect talks between Israel and Hamas are underway in Egypt based on President Donald Trump’s 20-point Gaza peace plan.
Negotiations are centred around securing a captive-prisoner swap deal and potential ceasefire.
Trump says they're confident a deal can be reached and that Hamas has been “agreeing to important things”. 

Al Jazeera's Senior political analyst, Marwan Bishara, says it's wishful thinking to believe Israel and Hamas will agree to all 20 points of Trump's plan.
